70.8	Oliver_Sacks	Oliver Sacks	Oliver Wolf Sacks, CBE (born 9 July 1933, London, England), is a British neurologist, psychologist and amateur chemist who has spent the major portion of his career in the United States. He lives in New York City, and is professor of neurology and psychiatry at Columbia University, where he also holds the position of "Columbia Artist". He previously spent many years on the clinical faculty of Yeshiva University's Albert Einstein College of Medicine.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/9.13.09OliverSacksByLuigiNovi.jpg/220px-9.13.09OliverSacksByLuigiNovi.jpg
